text.tspan: An array library for nested, variable-sized data,
including arbitrary-length lists, records, mixed types,
and missing data, using NumPy-like idioms.
Arrays are dynamically typed, but operations
on them are compiled and fast.
Compiled operations are performed on these data buffers, not the objects
An entire array consists of one small tree with large, contiguous data
buffers attached to each node (color coded with the above).
